.TH "send_break" 9 "send_break" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
send_break \- performed time break
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" send_break
.BI "(struct tty_struct *tty "  ","
.BI "unsigned int duration "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tty" 12
device to break on
.IP "duration" 12
timeout in mS

Perform a timed break on hardware that lacks its own driver level
timed break functionality.

Locking:
atomic_write_lock serializes
